column2: A simple HEK293 lysate, which can be used to benchmark the performance of both the LC system and the mass spectrometer. The four files uploaded here were aqcuired on different timepoints and show distinct LC column differences.
HEK293 lysate, digested with Trypsin, run on a 300 minute LC, measured on a Thermo Orbitrap Velos
column3: MaxQuant 1.5.2 with default parameters plus a second run using a maximal RT alignment window of 100 min (20 min default). Complete mqpar files are attached.
